body_html: @louisquinn I went through your test code with ssd_inception_v2_coco model from object detection zoo. I should have read the issue earlier :) Yes int32 ops are not available natively in TensorRT. It will be possible to convert object detection networks and others through plugin mechanism in near future with new TensorRT releases. Sorry for the inconvenience.
